          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": "3CPRNPC"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " K(L)Pu pulse reactor was a 3 layers of",
                "plutonium and uranium mixed sphere, and the average",
                "neutron energy was 1.59 MeV. CFBR was a multi shell",
                "enriched uranium quasi spherical structure with a",
                "reflective layer, and the average neutron energy was",
                "1.22 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Central fast neutron fluence rate of K(L)Pu",
                "was 4.99E8 /cm2/s/W. The diameter of the central",
                "cavity was 40 mm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Neutron spectrum of K(L)Pu pulse reactor centre cavity:",
                " Eg(MeV)   neutron flux(%)",
                " >3        16.08",
                " ~1.4      26.78",
                " ~0.9      15.04",
                " ~0.4      22.37",
                " ~0.1      16.72",
                " ~0.017    2.99",
                " ~0.003    0.0287",
                " ~0 0005   0.000177"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "235U electroplated sheet with stainless steel backing"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The ratio of 197Au(n,f) and 235(n,f) was",
                "measured on K(L)Pu and CFBR. The samples of Au and",
                "235U in diameter of 6 mm were placed in the upper and",
                "lower ionization chambers of a small \"back to back\"",
                "double ionization chamber with Ar gas and 300 V",
                "voltage. The samples were irradiated for 2 hours, and",
                "the K(L)Pu reactor power was 10 W. 235U fission count",
                "was recorded online. The activity of 198Au was",
                "measured offline with HPGe detector. On CFBR, the",
                "ionization chamber was wrapped with Cd, and the",
                "reactor power was 50 W. The ratio of 180Hf(n,g) and",
                "197(n,g). Hf foil in diameter of 18 mm was wrapped",
                "between Au foils, and placed in a approximately 40 mm",
                "square grid made of copper wire. The samples were",
                "irradiated on K(L)Pu for 4 hours, and power was 25",
                "W.The samples were irradiated on CFBR for 4 hours,",
                "and power was 200 W. The activity of 198Au and 181Hf",
                "was measured offline with HPGe detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
